Siphamandla Goge is following this story. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - SAPS Deputy National Commissioner Bonang Mgwenya appeared in court and was granted R20,000 bail. Lieutenant General Mgwenya, responsible for Human Resource Management, is accused of tender fraud. READ: Deputy police commissioner arrested Her arrest is related to an almost R200-million tender for police emergency warning equipment. Police Minister Bheki Cele says he's saddened by the arrest of senior police officials. A Deputy National Police Commissioner was arrested for fraud, corruption, theft and money laundering today. Courtesy #DStv403  Mgwenya joins several others who were previously arrested, including the former police commissioner, Khomotso Phahlane. "It's a sad feeling, no doubt about it," Police Minister Bheki Cele said. READ: Cele saddened by police arrests "With all the arrests, especially the latest arrests. Arrested [were] quite several senior police. "It's a situation that leaves you sad." Mgwenya and other officers are due back in court in November.